result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan Michael Coulter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: The defendant may not consume/possess any alcohol.

The defendant must follow any outpatient treatment plans that are currently in place.

The defendant must take all prescribed midications and only in the manner prescribed.

The defendant must obtain his GED.

Expungement authorized under 973.015.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Ryan Michael Coulter in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 2:41 pm. Have resolution. State DRI 1&2 and count 3 criminal damage to property - w/hold sentence and place on probation for 1 year with conditions - standard conditions - no employment or work search as on disability - take prescribed medications and only as prescribed - costs. Has complied with victim notification and the victim is in the court room and does not want to make statement. Court DRI counts 1 & 2. Count 3 amend to misdemeneanor criminal damage to property. Court reads new charges and penalties. Defendant pleads NC to count 3 as amended. Court goes thru plea questionnaire and finds that defendant is entering plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently by entering his plea and waiving his right to JT, factual basis, accepts plea and adjudges guility of count 3 as amended. State/Burns asks for expungement and state has no objection to expungement make statement follow joint recommendations. Coulter withholds statement. Victim now makes statement. Court sentences to following - count 3  w/hold sentence and place on probation for 1 year with following conditions: AODA and follow thru, no consumption/possession, follow any outpatient treatment plans by all providers, obtain GED, 50 hours community service, costs - Burns objects to $200 DNA surcharge being assessed - Court still imposes but objection is duly noted, take all prescribed medications and only in the manner prescribed. Appeal rights given. No jail credit. Authorize expungement 973.015.
Final pre-trial on January 21, 2015 at 02:15 pm.

Called at 2:07 PM. Ryan Coulter appears in person and with counsel Mary Burns. State appear by Jodie Bednar-Clemens. Burns provides court with waiver of PH form, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his right to PH, finds probable cause, binds over for trial. State has filed Information that mirrors the complaint. Burns has Information, waives reading of it, will proceed to ARGN, enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts pleas, continues bond, set for FPT on 1/21/15 at 2:15 PM.
